40px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 0px !important;}\"][vc_single_image image=\"791\" img_size=\"full\" alignment=\"center\" css=\".vc_custom_1532088918507{margin-top: 0px !important;margin-bottom: 0px !important;}\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][/vc_section]				','Cryptocurrency Market','\n				\n				Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscin elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore.				','publish','closed','closed','','cryptocurrency-market','','','2018-07-20 08:23:09','2018-07-20 08:23:09','',0,'https://alphaomegadigital.com.au/?post_type=case-studies&amp;p=750',0,'case-studies','',0),(7592,1,'2020-08-05 00:54:19','2020-08-05 00:54:19','','Image of google console','','inherit','open','closed','','stephen-phillips-hostreviews-co-uk-shr_xn8s8qu-unsplash-1','','','2020-08-05 01:08:27','2020-08-05 01:08:27','',7436,'http://alphaomegadigital.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/stephen-phillips-hostreviews-co-uk-shr_Xn8S8QU-unsplash-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(7601,1,'2020-08-05 01:05:45','2020-08-05 01:05:45','<!-- wp:image {\"id\":7516,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://alphaomegadigital.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Ignoring-online-marketing-is-like-opening-a-business-and-not-telling-a-soul_-1024x576.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7516\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:atomic-blocks/ab-drop-cap {\"dropCapFontSize\":2} -->\n<div style=\"color:#32373c\" class=\"wp-block-atomic-blocks-ab-drop-cap drop-cap-letter ab-font-size-2 ab-block-drop-cap\"><div class=\"ab-drop-cap-text\"><p>The internet is such a big part of our lives now and it has completely changed the way in which we bank, shop, consume media and socialise. </p></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:atomic-blocks/ab-drop-cap -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Newspaper and magazine have become mostly <a href=\"https://www.crikey.com.au/2020/05/04/australia-magazines-disruption-bauer/\">defunct</a> in Australia, as readership has dwindled and advertising costs have remained high; needless to say this means advertisers have been paying the same advertising rates for a lesser result.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>TV advertising has also taken a <a href=\"https://www.adnews.com.au/news/digital-ad-spend-to-overtake-tv-in-2017-studies-find\">hit</a>; once considered the gold standard of effective advertising in Australia, ad free streaming services such as Netflix and Stan have drawn audiences away from mainstream TV. Audiences for years were frustrated with the increasing amount of ads on TV, but they tolerated it when no other options were available. Streaming services have provided a solution to this problem, thus creating a mass exodus from commercial TV. This applies to the embattled <a href=\"https://www.adnews.com.au/news/news-corp-s-billion-dollar-write-down-for-foxtel#:~:text=News%20Corp%20has%20written%20down,nearly%20%24US1%20billion%20(AUD1.&amp;text=27%20billion%20(AUD3.,of%20%24US1%20billion%20(AUD1.\">Foxte</a>l as well.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>These events mean Australian businesses are spending more money than ever on digital marketing: in 2017 we spent 3.43 billion advertising online, and in 2019 we spent a whopping <a href=\"https://www.adnews.com.au/news/australian-brands-spent-9-4-billion-on-digital-ads-in-2019\">9.4 billion</a>, which is significantly higher than the previous forecast of 4.97 billion for <a href=\"https://www.adnews.com.au/news/digital-ad-spend-to-overtake-tv-in-2017-studies-find\">2019</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Aside from the obvious fact that digital marketing is now more effective than traditional media, it also offers a degree of transparency. You no longer have to place an ad and cross your fingers it works for you, all of the data is readily available through the many digital analytics platforms so you know exactly how each dollar translates into web traffic, social media traffic, engagement and sales. I use <a href=\"https://databox.com/\">databox</a> to track all of these metrics with clients. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There is one caveat to my previous statement though: although transparency and data are a surety in the digital age, none of those metrics are guaranteed to translate into sales for your business. This presents a problem to the everyday business owner who is running their own digital campaigns. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There is a sense of achievement and the feeling of being in control; you\'re spending money and you can see its resulting in extra likes to your page, more followers, more traffic, more page views. There is really only one question to ask yourself  at this point:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote {\"className\":\"is-style-large\"} -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote is-style-large\"><p>\"Are your current digital marketing efforts translating into sales?</p><p></p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If the answer is yes, then awesome keep doing what you\'re doing if you\'re happy with your figures. If the answer is no, then it\'s really time to engage with a professional to maximise the results you\'re getting for your ad spend. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>My goal when conducting digital campaigns for clients, at the very least is to cover my cost. That is the money you as the client spends on hiring me to manage your marketing is offset by the increase in results you attain from hiring a professional. This effect is also compounded by the fact that you now have a lot more time that you were spending on marketing, to other facets of your business. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:block {\"ref\":7586} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:columns -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\"><!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2